snippet.textDisplay:
I am amazed how restaurants with animal products being the main focus are still popular to some extent. I suppose you have seen an episode or two of kitchen nightmares. Everything wrong with the food is always the meat, it goes to waste because the chefs cannot properly prepare nor preserve it.

Gordon respects vegetarians and he supports vegetarian restaurants and that is really understandable after all he has seen and tasted. He even himself called the pile of chicken wings a mass grave, because that is what it is.

My problem is not the fact that meat is eaten, but how the meat is not respected or appreciated. It gets thrown into the fridge and is only taken out to let it rot, it seems.

If anyone reads this this far, I hope you are having a nice day. If you are in charge of your daily nutrition, I have something to recommend: More fruits, more salad and plant based protein. Tofu is good and with the rise of climate change awareness and popularity of vegetarianism, there are more and more vegan alternatives for the meals you are used to. Fast food chains are embracing vegan products as well. They may even be cheaper! Try them out. You won't be disappointed.
